<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6151&amp;p=62024#p62024"><![CDATA[
Note that on some of the levels, it's exceeding the 64 sprite limit instead of just the 8 sprite limit.  Each cat is 4 sprites, some levels have 20 cats.  One level (3-20) even has 30 cats, which is more than the GBA version's level designer allows you to place.<br /><br /><br />Edit:<br />I just tried out all those builds in Nintendulator, and they all fail miserably, drawing a bunch of random sprites in random places, but the sprites are okay in other emulators.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Sat May 29, 2010 2:50 am</p><hr />
